2.caption: 1967 East–West Pro Bowl
2.description: The 1967 Pro Bowl was the seventeenth annual National Football League (NFL) all-star game which featured the outstanding performers from the 1966 season. The game was played on January 22, 1967, in a heavy rainstorm at the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum in Los Angeles, California before a sparse crowd of 15,062. This was the second-lowest attendance in the history of the Pro Bowl next to the inaugural game in 1939. The final score was East 20, West 10. For the second year in a row, the East dominated the West on the strength of turnovers. They recovered two fumbles and intercepted four passes.
2.inspected:Co-MVPs: Gale Sayers (Chicago Bears), Floyd Peters (Philadelphia Eagles)
2.inspected:Stadium: Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum, Los Angeles, California
